        <h1>Effigy Entity & Mapper Framework</h1>
	</div>

<blockquote>Effigy: 1. a sculpture or model of a person. 2. a roughly made model of a particular person, made in order to be damaged or destroyed
as a protest or expression of anger</blockquote>

<p>You can decide which definition above fits with your standard data-access experience, but I generally find #2 to be appropriate when trying to do
simple quick work.</p>

<h2>Features</h2>

<p>Effigy provides two primary features:</p>

<ul>
    <li>Sql annotations to inject Spring-JDBC code into abstract methods in a simple and consistent manner using minimal code.</li>
    <li>Entity framework annotations which provide a simple and lightweight entity CRUD framework.</li>
</ul>

See the <a href="guide">User Guide</a> for in-depth documentation about all of the supported features.

